summary: I had this weird AM dream
title: I had this weird AM dream
body:
So in my dream/nightmare TJ and Cyrus began dating so TJ was like ‘Hey you should meet my mom, step dad and step sister’ so they set up this dinner to introduce Cyrus as his boyfriend. So TJ forgets to mention that his step sisters name is Iris, so Cyrus arrives and then down the stairs Iris walks in and screams when she sees Cyrus and Cyrus does the same thing. The two run in opposite direction screaming, cut to TJ looking confused. Then the three of them all sitting down at this weird big table with TJ’s mom which for some reason is my English teacher Mrs. Pearson then TJ’s step dad arrives, turns out its Metcalf, Cyrus screams again. But here is where it gets really weird so they begin to talk then the ghc and Jonah walk in and say that they are TJ’s step siblings, this time Cyrus faints and I woke up 

So I think there were drugs in my dinner

this is cyrus and tj telling them that they're dating 
cyrus: dad, sharon..we need...
body:
[cyrus has already come out to his parents]

this is cyrus and tj telling them that they’re dating

cyrus: dad, sharon..we need to tell you something

*sharon and norman share a look of concern towards each other*

sharon: what is it honey? *reaches across the table to hold cyrus’ hands*

cyrus: tj and i…we’re….uh..we’re dating

cyrus’ dad: we already kn- *gets pinched by sharon* ah!

sharon, whispers shouts: norman!

cyrus’ dad, in a serious voice: ah, well this is quite unexpected

sharon: this is truly a surprise

*cyrus and tj look at each other in confusion*

cyrus: okay what’s going on, be honest, why do you sound like you already knew

sharon, sighing: because we did already know…

cyrus: hOW?!

sharon: sweetie, you don’t look at your “just friends” the way you and tj look at each other

cyrus’ dad: and we can hear you giggling while you’re talking to tj on the phone at 10pm at night

*cue a flustered cyrus and tj*

cyrus: i…i..we don’t

cyrus’ dad: or that one time i saw you wearing tj’s hoodie, you put it up to your face and couldn’t stop smiling

cyrus: dAD

tj, holding back a laugh: i didn’t hear about the second part

sharon: and tj

*tj faces freezes*

sharon: anyone with two eyes can see how much you care for cyrus, your face lights up the second cyrus walks into the room, so much that you weren’t paying attention one time when you were helping me scrapbook and stuck the letter “A” on top of a picture of norman

tj and cyrus: *comeplely flustered and quiet*

cyrus’ dad: what we’re trying to say to you boys is…

sharon: …that we are completely and toally okay with you two dating

cyrus’ dad: it’s not often you meet someone they completes you in every way possible

cyrus: thanks dad, we..we really appreciate it

cyrus’ dad: so you’re staying for dinner right, tj?

tj: of course *smiles*

title: I’m Rewatching Andi Mack
body:
Here are some thoughts I had and highlights that should be talked about more from Episode 1: 

  • Cyrus’s “SaVagE” when he sees Andi’s bike is the most on-brand thing ever. 
  • Ya know how you all like to point out that rainbow tape came after cyrus on the opening sequence and buffy now has the rainbow jacket? It’s also right next to Jonah and I have literally never noticed

tea. 

  • Cyrus calling Celia Andi’s mom!!!!
  • Why have we forgotten about literally the entire storyline of Season 1, like, it was so pivotal and now it’s all about Tyrus. oh well. 
  • Enough about Andi’s bike, let’s talk about Bex’s entrance because PARALLELS BETWEEN MOTHER AND DAUGHTER
  • “YoU guYS its mY siST3r !1!1!” (sorry, I can’t get over the forgotten storyline)
  • “kissing asphalt on my hog” oh my goodness Cyrus no. 
  • Poor buffy has already had enough of the slayer jokes 5 minutes into S1 
  • all the art on Celia/Ham’s walls is uncharacteristic…
  • Also the entire house changed at some point (I never noticed, oops) 
  • “we sold all your toe rings at a garage sale” 
  • the music festival hahaha i forgot
  • we love a fit queen aka Celia
  • why is the box just laying RIGHT ON TOP OF THE COUCH though?
  • wow there’s been so much character development since E1 oh my goodness wow
  • Who knew pizza would end up becoming a thing? (the foreshadowing!!!) 
  • Andi stalking Jonah omg DEVELOPMENT
  • why Bex, why the Jonah date? Why? What ON EARTH made you think that this would be a good idea? I’m still baffled and haunted by this scene
  • “I never forget a foot” what.
  • Bex lookin like a proud mom 
  • and taking pictures that look like… an actual date as opposed to a freaking frisbee lesson
  • I haven’t seen Jonah this excited/happy in a while now that i think of it
  • Jonah’s face when andi says “i like you” is a mood
  • “Amber alert” still kills me a little ton
  • And now people ship ambi wow development
  • remember that one episode where they say they’re having their first argument but like??? Literally episode 1?? 
  • Never forget that Jonah texted first, and it wasn’t just emojis
  • The scene where Bex tells Andi she’s her mother is actually so raw, real, and pure, especially since I just finished Season 3
  • literally this entire scene
  • “I can’t be here right now” -Andi Mack, Season 1, Episode 1, and literally in every episode on.
  • “Yeah, I’m real torn up I can’t listen to Nickelback right now”-Bex Mack, 2017
  • Cyrus. Just…Cyrus…and his awkwardness I STAN
  • I’m kinda sad there was never like, an actual celebration or ANYTHING other than the frisbee lesson for her birthday but whatever.
  • Cyrus. oh. my. goodness. 
  • the Space Otters T-shirt wow
  • Condor? Did I miss something? Someone help.
  • Andi’s fashion has changed so much and I am HERE FOR IT
  • Okay so Celia seems kinda mean in this episode but I STAN Season 2 and 3 Celia, again, DEVELOPMENT
  • “Grandma”
  • I really want the hospital bracelets to pop back up later in Season 3…
  • The OG “Who wants pizza? 
  • Remember the pre-Bowie days? Me neither.
  • Wow Amber drama whatt.

Side note: I remember seeing this episode for the very first time and continually confusing Jonah and Cyrus. Thank u for coming to my TED talk.
